description:
The Lazy Chef - Series 1, Episode 2

The Lazy Chef's next stop is the picturesque county of Mayo. The mix of flat terrain, rolling mountains and rugged coastline offer up the perfect conditions for some of the ingredients featured in this second episode, including fish and mountain lamb. Simon gets straight to work for his dinner as he fishes in the Atlantic Ocean, catching some wonderful mackerel and pollock. He rustles up a quick lunch of mackerel on the cliffs of Clare Island. Then it's straight to the kitchen to prepare his effortless Sticky Fish Noodles that will satisfy any busy family.




Original Air Date: 23-Oct-2014
